entries.femaleVariant: 'Member when there was cars for days down there. Engines roarin', horns honkin' day an' night.
Now look at it. Empty. Quiet.
Kids used to sit on this bridge, get hit with a cloud of gas, that's how many of 'em there were.
How the world goes. Quiet, like.
Eh, world's done gone already. We just wasn't lookin'.
